Patch Set 2: Code-Review-1

According to the OpenStack style guidelines, when catching an exception you should be as specific so you don’t mistakenly catch unexpected exceptions. I think catching all errors from a deriving class might give us a harder time debugging and catching unsuspecting bugs.

Patch Set 4: Code-Review+1

LGTM, overall.
It seems that we also need further refactoring for this piece of functionality. IMO, it would be better to have some dictionary that contained mapping between GlanceExceptions and HTTPExceptions. It allows us to remove all these excepts clauses and catch the exception only in one place. After that we would fetch the proper exception from dict and return it to user.
